storyInfo: Half a year has already passed since the members of Team Rainbow were unexpectedly transported to Terra. After recovering from their initial surprise, they gradually adjust to life in the new land.

attributes.content: Mission log day 184.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: Currently, we are still holding fast in this run-down house.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: The 184th day of the mission and the 27th day of reaching the aforementioned run-down house.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: Who would believe that we've already lived in this place for 184 days.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: We still have no clues about this world.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: Two weeks ago, based on instructions from the locals, we left this run-down house and headed to another town.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: Before we left, the townspeople said that it was a 'more developed place.' I am unsure if our definitions of developed are the same.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: What happened? Turns out it was a bandit den.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: No batteries, no useful information, not even a single person we could communicate normally with.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: Of course, we didn't leave empty-handed. Tina 'acquired' a car.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: The process was long and arduous, and used up much of what little supplies and ammunition we still had.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: However, the car was heavily damaged during the conflict, and broke down soon after we returned to the house.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: Alexsandr tried to repair the car, but this car didn't have an obvious fuel intake point, and on further inspection even the fuel tank was absent.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: The engine's structure was completely incomprehensible to him, to the point he wasn't even sure if it was actually an engine.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: The only good news was that it was a left-hand drive car.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: Having been in this world for half a year by now, we are very certain that this place is not Earth.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: Stealing cars and getting into gunfights, it's like we're fugitives in a post-apocalyptic film.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: Those bandits with long lizard tails didn't even need to use guns, as they were able to throw javelins weighing up to 10 kilograms to a distance tens of meters away. The term gunfight may not be accurate here.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: Some of them could even create huge fireballs from thin air and launch them, with the effect somewhere in between a grenade and an RPG.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: This world is far too abnormal, to the point where I'm no longer surprised by anything.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: The adaptability of humans often exceeds my expectations. It seems that we will continue to struggle to survive here.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: Today will be the last day I'm recording. I don't plan on recording anymore.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: The storage for this recorder is almost full, and the battery will not last much longer.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: Our only source of power on this world is Tina's solar charger. Thank goodness this world has a sun as well.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: What would happen if this charger broke, or if we used up all our supplies and ammunition?
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: To be frank, I don't know.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: This situation still feels unreal to me, with everything being so weird......yet so natural.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: Which way is the path back home?
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: Come on, Uman, look at this.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: Hey, you don't eat vegetables?
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: Let me see what else I have here......
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: What are you doing?
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: Haa! Come and look at Uman, my little buddy.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: You're raising a......what's this called again?
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: Originium slug, that's what the locals call these things.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: You still have the mood to raise this?
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: Why not? I'm spending all day sitting on the roof after all, might as well find something to do. Can't be talking to my machine gun all the time.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: Your job is to keep aware of the surrounding area's safety, not play around with this snail thing.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: What you've said makes sense, but what are we guarding against? Those quivering Infected, or the townsfolk living a kilometer away who never come here anyway?
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: The only living thing that's come close to this dump of a house is a flying lizard, which I suppose helped out with the ration issue.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: ......Where's Tina and Kötz?
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: They went to exchange supplies with those Infected people.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: Tina managed to hunt some stuff again yesterday. She's becoming pretty experienced at it.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: Tina went out to hunt by herself again?
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: Of course, she's even enjoying it. She's been trying to capture a wild burdenbeast.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: By the way, Kötz went to the town.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: Remember that thing I dismantled from the car? Kötz said he knows a mechanic in town and wanted to ask about it.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: Fine.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: You're too anxious, Cohen.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: Just relax, we can't return anytime soon anyway.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: Learn from Kötz and go talk with those people. They're somewhat friendly, at least.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: I still haven't learned the local language. Man, Kötz really knows his stuff.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: That's what I'm afraid of.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: Afraid of what?
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: Kötz is getting too close to those people. It isn't a good thing, the atmosphere around here is very abnormal.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: That town is too full of contradictions. We've been here for nearly a month, don't tell me you haven't picked up on that.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: A local government official who stays in his manor all day and never leaves......Oh, I guess the proper term is 'lord'? There's those fully-armed private soldiers of his as well.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: And this 'infected zone'.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: The entire region is governed by the same lord, yet these Infected are not allowed to live in the town. Even the other townsfolk are unwilling to approach this place.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: They were driven here.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: That's because these friends 'got a strange sickness'.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: The act of separating the sick when an infectious disease is raging about is not uncommon after all, even in the past. At least the lord did not just lock them all up in prison.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: Originium sickness......or was it Oripathy? I don't remember the exact term.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: All we know about this sickness is that it is related to Originium, it is infectious and it is incurable.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: But how does it actually spread between people? What does it being incurable actually mean?
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: No one's answered our questions, and assume that we should know the basic situation.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: This disease is either common sense in this town, or it is common sense in this world.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: If it is only contact with Originium ore that will cause problems, then I don't think that it is necessary to carry out quarantine measures.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: Besides, the doctor also thinks that there is no risk of infection from our frequency and distance of interaction with these Infected.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: This infected zone is just a wall-less prison, breeding hate between the Infected and the townsfolk. You can feel it even without seeing it for yourself.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: The word I'm using is 'hate', not just exclusion and discrimination. Hate is carved into every word they speak, every action they do. It's become part of their culture.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: Hate. You understand what I mean? This isn't just a problem about an unknown disease anymore. We shouldn't get involved in any local conflicts.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: Just imagine this scenario. If the townsfolk began grabbing torches, raising pitchforks and rushing into these Infected's homes, what would you do then? Shoot them down?
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: Hard to say.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: We have them to thank for our food, water and medicine for the past few months.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: Before this, we've been trudging back and forth across this treacherous wasteland, being attacked by anything that moves and not getting even a single glimpse of civilization......until we got their help.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: Do you really think we can just 'mind our own business', Cohen?
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: If they grabbed weapons and broke into Doctor Miarow's clinic, do you really want to just stand aside and watch?
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: As for the problem you mentioned earlier, I don't think the infectiousness can be ignored.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: It's as if everyone in this world has undergone professional chemical warfare training. They are always covering up their nose and mouth, and being extremely sensitive about protecting their respiratory systems, no matter their age or gender.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: I've repeated this point before as well, that we must prepare similar protections for ourselves......
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: The doctor also approved of us keeping our distance. Thankfully the Infected don't have any complaints towards this. Perhaps this is normal to them.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: What did the doctor say about this?
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: I didn't ask him. None of us asked him.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: Every time we mention this topic, he always looks as though he would rather avoid it completely. As long as he thinks our defensive measures are fine, I won't bother him about it.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: (Shhh...)
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: 'I did not order pizza.'
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: There's no need to match passwords, Miss Cohen.
It's me, Miarow.
Right on cue.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: Hold on, let me open the door.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: Good morning, doctor.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: Good morning, Miss Cohen.
attributes.name: Miarow

attributes.content: Good morning, Mister Alexsandr.
attributes.name: Miarow

attributes.content: Heh, we were just talking about you.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: You do realize you're raising an Originium Slug, Mister Alexsandr?
attributes.name: Miarow

attributes.content: Yeah, this little thing is actually pretty fun to play with. Tina caught some earlier and this one was too small, so I kept it.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: So you came to look for Tina?
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: No, I'm here to deliver stuff.
attributes.name: Miarow

attributes.content: These are medical supplies, there were more leftovers this time.
attributes.name: Miarow

attributes.content: Thank you very much, doctor. We're always imposing on you.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: I should be the one thanking you. It's all thanks to those Originium Slugs Miss Tina caught that we have enough painkillers for the next few months.
attributes.name: Miarow

attributes.content: So, these 'Originium Slugs' really can cure diseases?
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: How do I put it...
attributes.name: Miarow

attributes.content: Oripathy is incurable......This remedy made by fermenting the body fluids of Originium Slugs can only help to relieve the pain, it cannot actually cure the disease.
attributes.name: Miarow

attributes.content: However, being able to relieve the pain is already a great blessing to the Infected. Crystallization on the skin will affect normal life, and the pain is so unbearable for some that they cannot even move.
attributes.name: Miarow

attributes.content: It's great that we can be of help.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: This is the book that you asked me to look for you last time. I specifically looked for one in the Ursus language.
attributes.name: Miarow

attributes.content: Oh, great. Let me take a look.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: Right......
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: Can you understand it?
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: ......With some difficulty.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: At a glance, it looks like Cyrillic.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: But when I look closer at it, there are many differences.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: At least you have something to do now, just treat it as learning a foreign language.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: It should be more interesting than playing with a snail.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: Speaking of language, what do you call the language we're speaking now?
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: Your accents are a little weird......
attributes.name: Miarow

attributes.content: But it is undoubtedly the Victorian language.
attributes.name: Miarow

attributes.content: Victoria......
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: What about the locals, what do they speak?
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: The people here speak Sargonian, though Sargonian itself has a lot of dialects.
attributes.name: Miarow

attributes.content: For example, most Sargons can't understand the Sargonian spoken by the tribes from the rainforest in east Sargon.
attributes.name: Miarow

attributes.content: That's complicated.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: Ursus.......Ursus.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: What kind of place is Ursus?
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: Right......
attributes.name: Miarow

attributes.content: I'm not too sure myself......
attributes.name: Miarow

attributes.content: Back in school, they used to say that Ursus was in the far north and covered in snow year-round. It's ruled by a Tsar.
attributes.name: Miarow

attributes.content: But I don't know anyone who's ever been to Ursus, haha.
attributes.name: Miarow

attributes.content: Tsar? ...Tch.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: What's wrong, you seem disappointed.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: A little.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: If I have the chance, I'd really like to take a look at this place called Ursus.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: Travelling to faraway places......that sounds nice.
attributes.name: Miarow

attributes.content: Perhaps only great people like you are able to do it.
attributes.name: Miarow

attributes.content: If possible, I also hope to travel to Columbia to complete my studies and become a real doctor.
attributes.name: Miarow

attributes.content: Alas, I don't have that much money, and the patients here still need me.
attributes.name: Miarow

attributes.content: You're still young, there's always a chance in the future.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: ......Maybe.
attributes.name: Miarow

attributes.content: Oh right, there's one other thing.
attributes.name: Miarow

attributes.content: Please don't go outside for a while, and hide that car of yours as well.
attributes.name: Miarow

attributes.content: What happened?
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: Did something happen in town?
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: How did you know?
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: Last night, I saw the lord's soldiers patrolling by the wall. That was unusual.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: Actually, the lord's soldiers have been doing night patrols in the infected zone for a week now......
attributes.name: Miarow

attributes.content: Recently, monsters have been appearing in town. They've attacked many people.
attributes.name: Miarow

attributes.content: Monsters?
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: Man, all the animals in this world are already so strange, I don't dare imagine what a monster would be like.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: The townsfolk have been complaining about the Infected lately. Do you want to move to the second floor of my clinic for a few days? The lord's soldiers will come to inspect this ruined house sooner or later.
attributes.name: Miarow

attributes.content: Will it be fine, doctor? It might bring you trouble.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: You've helped me out so much, I don't think it's a big deal.
attributes.name: Miarow

attributes.content: I agree with the doctor. Clashing with the lord's soldiers will just get us involved in the local issues and bring more trouble upon us.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: I don't want to get into a fight with those two-meter tall dog-head people.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: (Cough) Err, I'll tell you about that next time.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: Someone's coming.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: 'I did not order pizza.'
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: Alexsandr! Open the door!
attributes.name: Frost

attributes.content: It's Tina.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: Hold on.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: Calm down, what happened?
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: Cohen! Trouble.
attributes.name: Frost

attributes.content: A group of armed townsfolk are blocking the road to the infected zone, and the Infected are confronting them.
attributes.name: Frost

attributes.content: Those people are acting very aggressively, demanding that someone be handed over to them.
attributes.name: Frost

attributes.content: You see, what did I say earlier?
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: ......Speak of the devil......
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: Townsfolk? Armed?
attributes.name: Miarow

attributes.content: Why? The lord's soldiers do not allow normal townsfolk to approach the infected zone.
attributes.name: Miarow

attributes.content: That just means the lord's soldiers no longer have the time to care about this place anymore.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: Wait! What about Kötz? Didn't Kötz go to the town this morning?
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: Kötz said he was going to look for a mechanic in town this morning, but he hasn't returned yet.
attributes.name: Frost

attributes.content: Oh no.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: What do we do?
attributes.name: Frost

attributes.content: Go check it out first. At least make sure if Kötz is there.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: Should we bring weapons?
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: ......Bring them just in case, but don't attack unless absolutely necessary.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: Alright.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: No! Wait.
attributes.name: Miarow

attributes.content: Don't worry, let me handle it first. I'm more familiar with the townsfolk, let me negotiate with them.
attributes.name: Miarow

attributes.content: ......Alright, doctor. Please be careful.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: It's fine, the townsfolk......They're reasonable.
attributes.name: Miarow

attributes.content: Hand that person over!
attributes.name: Townsfolk

attributes.content: Give us that suspicious person! All of us saw it!
attributes.name: Townsfolk

attributes.content: What the hell are you talking about!
attributes.name: Infected Townsfolk

attributes.content: Don't lie to us, you damn pollutants! I know all the recent happenings were you guys' doings!
attributes.name: Townsfolk

attributes.content: You ungrateful maggots, the lord should never have allowed you to stay! !
attributes.name: Townsfolk

attributes.content: I saw a large and heavily wrapped up person leave town and sneak over here earlier! Hand him over!
attributes.name: Townsfolk

attributes.content: I don't know what you're talking about!
attributes.name: Infected Townsfolk

attributes.content: Fine, since you refuse to give up this false pretense, we don't need to be courteous anymore.
attributes.name: Townsfolk

attributes.content: Everyone! Get them!
attributes.name: Townsfolk

attributes.content: Don't you dare! Do you really think we're pushovers!
attributes.name: Infected Townsfolk

attributes.content: Everyone! They want a fight!
attributes.name: Infected Townsfolk

attributes.content: Hey, stop! Don't fight! Let's talk first, alright?
attributes.name: Blitz

attributes.content: Wah! Mister Kötz, didn't I ask you to hide......
attributes.name: Infected Townsfolk

attributes.content: It's fine, don't worry. Let me talk with them.
attributes.name: Blitz

attributes.content: This accent, you're not from here!
attributes.name: Townsfolk

attributes.content: Who are you!
attributes.name: Townsfolk

attributes.content: (Sigh......What do I do now. )
attributes.name: Blitz

attributes.content: Ahem.
attributes.name: Blitz

attributes.content: Blitz: I'm a merchant, one that collects trash.
attributes.name: Blitz

attributes.content: Merchant? If you're a merchant, why do you have to sneak around?
attributes.name: Townsfolk

attributes.content: What do you have under that bulging robe of yours? Come on, show us!
attributes.name: Townsfolk

attributes.content: Capture him! Bring him to the lord!
attributes.name: Townsfolk

attributes.content: Fine fine fine, I'll listen to you. I'll go with you guys.
attributes.name: Blitz

attributes.content: There's no reason for us to fight, right? I'll explain clearly to your 'lord'.
attributes.name: Blitz

attributes.content: Mister Kötz......
attributes.name: Infected Townsfolk

attributes.content: Capture these guys as well. I suspect they're all accomplices!
attributes.name: Townsfolk

attributes.content: You! Don't go too far! What right do you have to capture others!
attributes.name: Infected Townsfolk

attributes.content: Oh, come on.
attributes.name: Blitz

attributes.content: Bro, that's pretty unreasonable of you.
attributes.name: Blitz

attributes.content: These friends just bought some Originium Slugs that I hunted. Surely it's not a crime to sell Originium Slugs?
attributes.name: Blitz

attributes.content: Who knows if you people are colluding together to plan something sinister.
attributes.name: Townsfolk

attributes.content: Capture them......capture all of them!
attributes.name: Townsfolk

attributes.content: Stop! Are you all planning to go against Lord Tulla's will!
attributes.name: Miarow

attributes.content: Doctor! You've finally come!
attributes.name: Infected Townsfolk

attributes.content: Ah......apologies, Doctor Miarow.
attributes.name: Blitz

attributes.content: Lord Tulla ruled that no one is allowed to approach this zone, unless you are an Infected as well.
attributes.name: Miarow

attributes.content: What, are all of you Infected?
attributes.name: Miarow

attributes.content: Don't bother trying to smooth-talk us. What kind of relationship do you have with this outsider? Spit it out!
attributes.name: Burly Townsfolk

attributes.content: Otherwise, we'll capture you as well.
attributes.name: Burly Townsfolk

attributes.content: He's a patient of mine. There's no rule that my clinic cannot accept outsiders as patients.
attributes.name: Miarow

attributes.content: Well then, since you want to stop me, why don't you try and see?
attributes.name: Burly Townsfolk

attributes.content: ......What are you planning to do?
attributes.name: Miarow

attributes.content: Don't waste time here, bring them away.
attributes.name: Strange Townsfolk

attributes.content: ......Hold on!
attributes.name: Miarow

attributes.content: You......you're not from this town!
attributes.name: Miarow

attributes.content: What do you think of it?
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: The doctor is trying to reason with them, but the other side are stubborn as bulls.
attributes.name: Frost

attributes.content: Doesn't seem like it can be resolved peacefully.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: Don't be rash, let the doctor handle it.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: Cohen, something's wrong.
attributes.name: Frost

attributes.content: Huh?
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: Do you see those big guys at the back there?
attributes.name: Frost

attributes.content: I see them.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: What are those things they're carrying? They're wrapped in cloth.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: With that size, it doesn't seem like they're farming tools.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: Would normal farmers carry these kinds of heavy weapons?
attributes.name: Frost

attributes.content: ......Even in this world, I don't think farmers would till the fields while carrying huge swords.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: They're not here to talk, Cohen.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: Don't do anything stupid!
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: ......Both of you cover me.
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: Understood.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: Brat, shut your mouth if you don't want to die.
attributes.name: Strange Townsfolk

attributes.content: You're not from here.
attributes.name: Miarow

attributes.content: I've never seen you before. Who are you people!
attributes.name: Miarow

attributes.content: What are you planning to do here!
attributes.name: Miarow

attributes.content: Huh, you guys are just like thieves crying 'stop thief'!
attributes.name: Infected Townsfolk

attributes.content: Guards! There are intruders here! Guards!
attributes.name: Infected Townsfolk

attributes.content: Everyone! There are intruders!
attributes.name: Infected Townsfolk

attributes.content: Tch.
attributes.name: Strange Townsfolk

attributes.content: You talk too much.
attributes.name: Strange Townsfolk

attributes.content: Time to shut up.
attributes.name: Sarkaz Mercenary

attributes.content: Doctor, get down!
attributes.name: Blitz

attributes.content: Guns!
attributes.name: Sarkaz Mercenary

attributes.content: They're mercenaries!
attributes.name: Sarkaz Mercenary

attributes.content: Why are there mercenaries in the infected zone?
attributes.name: Sarkaz Mercenary

attributes.content: Don't worry about it. We have to bring them all back, dead or alive.
attributes.name: Sarkaz Mercenary

attributes.content: Do it.
attributes.name: Sarkaz Mercenary

attributes.content: Don't even think about it!
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: Lord! Cover fire!
attributes.name: Ash

attributes.content: Should have done so from the start.
attributes.name: Tachanka

attributes.content: Taste this (Russian profanity)!
attributes.name: Tachanka
